      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.92,
      "end": 11.72,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.02,
      "end": 16.32,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, the blacksmith and his dog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.58,
      "end": 21.94,
      "text": "A blacksmith had a little dog which used to sleep when his master was at work,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.44,
      "end": 25.02,
      "text": "but was very wide awake indeed when it was time for meals.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.78,
      "end": 28.9,
      "text": "One day his master pretended to be disgruntled at this,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.38,
      "end": 32.34,
      "text": "and when he had thrown him a bone as usual, he said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.86,
      "end": 35.3,
      "text": "What on earth is the good of a lazy curl like you?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 35.88,
      "end": 39.64,
      "text": "When I am hammering away at my anvil, you just curl up and go to sleep.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 40.34,
      "end": 45.46,
      "text": "But no sooner do I stop for a mouthful of food than you wake up and wag your tail to be fed.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 46.32,
      "end": 49.26,
      "text": "Those who will not work deserve to starve.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 50.38,
      "end": 53.72,
      "text": "End of the blacksmith and his dog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 53.72,
      "end": 53.9,
      "text": "End of the blacksmith's Fables, the blacksmith and his dog.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
